      "width": 820,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## GitHub Repo Node Class\n\nThis graph now separates two levels clearly:\n\n- **Class graph surfaces**: the declaration, overview, and icon surfaces that describe the class itself\n- **Instance contract surfaces**: the editor/detail/summary/icon views used by actual `github-repo` node instances\n\nV1 scope stays narrow:\n\n- repo identity as `owner` + `repo`\n- optional `branch`\n- `homeRef` bootstrap fallback to `/root.node`\n- declaration-first home semantics\n\nNot in v1:\n\n- installation/write-status UX\n- repo introspection\n- README parsing\n- file-tree browsing"
      }
    }
